subject: WIP - ASL0623-CR0975 S/W V2000 LSZDC - Improve Limiter Performance
commitMessage:
WIP - ASL0623-CR0975 S/W V2000 LSZDC - Improve Limiter Performance

1) Upto 10ms Delay added to audio - to allow Limiter to start fading before
audio processed.
2) Voltage Limiter Threshold blocked at 102V to prevent amplifier noise.
3) Ability to change Surveillance Frequency Removed - For Code-Space
Reasons
4) Stack and Heap size decreased from 8192 to 4096 to free up RAM for
delay buffer.
5) Output clipping removed as saturated by shift. Unnecessary.

Patch-Set-2:
6) Delay reduced to 0.25ms (to be used with 0.1ms Attack)
7) Limiter Attack/Release updated to be logarithmic.

Patch-Set-3:
8) Delay parameters moved to Limiter function.
9) Stack-Size replaced to 8192
10) If new sample gives a target gain within 0.05dB of previous target,
the Hold-Count is reset - as might as well be the same level (prevents
premature release!) - Improves audio quality below 100Hz
11) Delay time reduced to 0.104ms (10 samples)
12) Recommended Time-Constants: A: "1" (0.1ms/-20.0dB), H: "20" (20ms), R: "10" (10ms/20.0dB)

Patch-Set-4:
13) Reset Maximum Limiter Threshold to 110V

Change-Id: Ib16c615bded78271c72293938ac2ccd3df891a14

subject: ASL0632-ID5234 Unload unnecessary plugins from modules
commitMessage:
ASL0632-ID5234 Unload unnecessary plugins from modules

Take #2 - the initial commit would unload too much. This commit ensures
that the Qt plugin and library mechanism keeps correct ref counts on the
plugins and only unloads module that really aren't required.

The problem was that the GUI plugins and headless plugins were loaded the
same way - they would load ALL plugins and only unload plugins not meant
for them - so because they are loaded in the same exe (workstation GUI) -
the effect was that GUI plugins would be loaded by the GUI plugin manager,
and then unloaded by the headless plugin manager.

By retaining instances of QPluginLoaders (not just locally scoped), we
get to use the ref counting facility of Qt to ensure that when a GUI plugin
is genuinely loaded and retained in one manager, it's ref count stays at one,
then when the headless plugin manager loads - and tries to unloaded a GUI
plugin - it's ref count goes to 2, then to 1, so it never actually unloads
it.

Change-Id: I5a44ba7447a0307a4e6ea434e474acfbbdec5e22
